snippet: East Timor advanced to the second round of World Cup qualifying for the first time, but fans are raising questions about how the team was put together.
abstract: Fans of East Timor national soccer team, which advanced to second round of World Cup qualifying for the first time, are angry that lineup consists of mostly Brazilian-born players;  national soccer teams that compete in World Cup are limited to native players, distinction East Timor has seemingly ignored.
lead_paragraph: East Timor advanced to the second round of World Cup qualifying for the first time, but fans are raising questions about how the team was put together.

headline.print_headline: Success No Longer Foreign, Thanks to Players Who Are
headline.main: Success Is No Longer Foreign to East Timor, but the Players Are
